      "writtenOn": "2016-04-08T21:55:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That would definitely lock things down a bit and make this a less scary API. I think that\u0027s a good idea.\n\nOne problem is that an intended use is that a second browser process starting up (which would get its own crashpad_handler) tries to rendezvous with the first, realizes the first is hung, and then wants to call this API on the first browser.\n\nIn that case, it that won\u0027t work because the two processes will have been registered with different crashpad_handler instances. So, we\u0027d have to figure out a way to have the second browser connect to the first\u0027s crashpad_handler.",
      "parentUuid": "cb5f5626_6a1c57b3",
      "revId": "930a4e5b5feee92cb7faad15cf05d5ed14c1f7b3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
